##

EXAMPLE: grouped_conditional_and_grouped_loop_logic.stult

This example checks that a conditional may begin with a grouped expression
without being mistaken for a loop.

The first statement starts with touching "((", but it is not a loop header.
It should parse as a conditional because the full expression is:

	(A & B) | (C & D)

A loop using the same grouped condition would need another pair of parentheses:

	(((A & B) | (C & D))) {
		...
	}

##

PRINT : STD["IO"]["PRINT"]

A : \/
B : /\
C : \/
D : \/

((A & B) | (C & D)) {
	PRINT("grouped conditional")
}

LOOP_ITERATIONS : 10
loop_counter : 0

(((A & B) | (C & D))) {
	(loop_counter = LOOP_ITERATIONS) {
		^
	}

	@loop_counter :+ 1
},{
	PRINT("grouped loop")
}